CUT each tortilla into 6 wedges. Place wedges in a single layer on a baking sheet; sprinkle with salt. BAKE at 350 degrees for 6 minutes or until crisp. Set aside. COOK beans and next 3 ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat 5 minutes, or until thoroughly heated; keep warm. ARRANGE tortilla wedges around 2 plates; layer half of bean mixture, 1 egg, and half of remaining ingredients in the center of each plate.